  "title": "Aurelius, Meditations §aur_12_xxii: Herein doth consist happiness of life, for a man to know thoroughly the true ...",
  "body": "Herein doth consist happiness of life, for a man to know thoroughly the true nature of everything; what is the matter, and what is the form of it: with all his heart and soul, ever to do that which is just, and to speak the truth. What then remaineth but to enjoy thy life in a course and coherence of good actions, one upon another immediately succeeding, and never interrupted, though for never so little a while?",
